text:
There is a variable called `locale`  it contains the language information that you can use for printing custom text:

```{% if locale == 'de' %}
  {{ translation.de_translation }}
{% else %}
  {{ translation_text }}
{% endif %}```
Personally I use HubDB for listin general translations. It's much easier for customer to change texts in HubDB.

```&lt;div class="d-flex align-items-center"&gt;
	{% if content.blog_post_author.avatar %}
	&lt;div class="avatar"&gt;
		&lt;img src="{{ content.blog_post_author.avatar }}" alt="{{ content.blog_post_author.full_name }}" /&gt;
	&lt;/div&gt;
	{% endif %}
	&lt;div class="meta"&gt;
		{% if content.blog_post_author %}
		&lt;span class="author"&gt;Post by
			&lt;a class="author-link" href="{{ group.absolute_url }}/author/{{ content.blog_post_author.slug }}"&gt;{{ content.blog_post_author.display_name }}&lt;/a&gt;
		&lt;/span&gt;
		{% endif %}
	&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;```

```.align-items-center {
  -ms-flex-align: center !important;
  align-items: center !important;
}
.d-flex {
  display: -ms-flexbox !important;
  display: flex !important;
}
.avatar {
  max-width: 100px;
  margin-right: 1rem;
}
.avatar img {
  border-radius: 10px;
}
.meta {
  line-height: 1.2;
}```
